# Small, static, checked-in seed reference table (D-12 FX conversion, ADR-005 Add #1) — not a
# generated artifact and not real/downloaded data, so it belongs in the "never ignore" carve-out
# alongside seed/fixtures/, same reasoning, different directory (built by seed/build_fx_rates.py
# once, then committed like a fixture — nothing regenerates or overwrites it on a normal run).
!seed/artifacts/fx_rates.csv
# Same gap, same fix, one day later (2026-07-17): dim_customer_xwalk.csv (ADR-005/D-04, the
# conformed MDM crosswalk every Gold table joins through) was never committed either — caught
# live by a Databricks git_source Gold run (job 127330185225331) FileNotFoundError, the local
# dev environment masked it the same way it masked fx_rates.csv's gap until real CI/cluster
# execution exercised the git-sourced checkout. Same carve-out reasoning: deterministic,
# built once by seed/build_xwalk.py, not real/downloaded data, not regenerated on a normal run.
!seed/artifacts/dim_customer_xwalk.csv

